A real estate firm, Life Page has restated its commitment to developing accessible homes by 2041. Chief Executive Officer of Life Page, Mr. Oladipupo Clement, reaffirmed this during an event organised for sales partners, investors, staff members, customers and guests to celebrate the end of a successful business year. While thanking investors and customers for their patronage over the past nine years, he urged them to take advantage of the investment and housing opportunities by the company to make homeownership easy for everyone. This, he said, is in tandem with the firm’s long-term goal to develop one million affordable homes. He said: “The company will continue to create more platforms to improve the standard of living, as well as help to fund and improve customers’ lifestyle with her products and offers.” Life Page at the event announced winners of its end of the year bounty offer at the Hall of Fame. It is also an avenue to celebrate outstanding partners and appreciate hard-working staff members. The company began the promotion in October, where customers, who subscribed to any product from N1, 000,000 stands a chance of winning fantastic prizes like a 10-year mortgage plan, N1 million N500, 000 cash prizes.  This promise was fulfilled at the event as winners of the bounty offer were selected through a raffle draw. Ifeoluwa Oriyomi, Mrs. Adedayo Olukoya, Mr Aniefiok Akpan were the lucky winner of a 10-year interest-free Mortgage (two-bedroom apartment, Almond County, Mowe), N1 Million only and N500, 000 only respectively. The partners got a two-bedroom apartment, an exotic car, weekend getaways at a resort and trips overseas. The firm also rolled out new products that offer 50 per cent Return on Investment (ROI). The Executive Director, Sales, Mr. Francis Ajilore, reiterated the benefits of the new offers. Meanwhile, construction works are in top gear at the Orange Terraces in Millennium Estate, Gbagada; Almond County, Mowe; Acacia, Lakowe.